The course includes lectures and practical trainings. Etiological factors, pathogenesis and characteriatic features of treatment of dental-,pulpal-, periodontal- and oral mucosal diseases in children will be covered during the course. Changes of dental tissues which occur during development will be covered. The course of caries, its affecting factors, different stages of caries and their treatment in decidous-, changing- and permanent teeth and in the period of root formation. The diagnostics and treatment methods of childhood periodontitis including agressive periodontitis will be covered. Various diseases will be learned which have mucosal clinical signs. More frequent changes of oral mucosa associated with infectious diseases will be covered in detail. Traumatic injuries of the teeth will be covered.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to give basic knowledge of oral and dental diseases in children.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows development and age-specific characteristics in children
2) knows etiology of mineralisation in decidous-, changing and permanent teeth

The aim of the subject is to give basic knowledge of oral and dental diseases in children. Students who have passed the course must know how to diagnose and treat diseses of dental hard tissues, pulpitis and periodontal abscess in decidous-, changing and permanenet teeth. Students have to diagnose the changes in periodontium and oral mucosa and know how to treat these changes.
